cadIpdrMib.name: cadIpdrMib

revisions.description: Expanded list of service types to align with latest CM-SP-OSSIv3.0-I23-140403.
Changed range of cadIpdrServicePriority from 0..10 to 0..64.
Added the IPDR 3.0 Mib objects for tracking session collector status.
Added the following new MIB object cadIpdrSessionId.
Change MAX-ACCESS of the following MIB object to read-only cadIpdrCollectorIpAddrType.
change MAX-ACCESS of the following MIB objects to read-create cadIpdrCollectorIpAddrType, cadIpdrCollectorPort, cadIpdrCollectorStatus, cadIpdrReportInterval, and cadIpdrReportStatus

cadIpdrMib.contactinfo: Arris Technical Support Postal: ARRIS E-Mail: support@arris.com
cadIpdrMib.description: This MIB modules contains the definitions to support configuration and status for C4 IPDR implementation.

cadIpdrExportEnabled.name: cadIpdrExportEnabled
cadIpdrExportEnabled.description: IPDR streams is enabled or disabled. When enabled the cadIpdrQueryPort and cadIpdrStreamingPort will be open to listen for collector connections. When disabled, all ports will be closed.

cadIpdrQueryPort.name: cadIpdrQueryPort
cadIpdrQueryPort.description: UDP port used to listen for collector queries.

cadIpdrStreamingPort.name: cadIpdrStreamingPort
cadIpdrStreamingPort.description: TCP port used to listen for collector connections.

cadIpdrDataAckWindow.name: cadIpdrDataAckWindow
cadIpdrDataAckWindow.description: Maximum number of unacknowledged IPDR/SP messages that may be outstanding to the collector. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrDataAckTimeout.name: cadIpdrDataAckTimeout
cadIpdrDataAckTimeout.description: Maximum elapsed time before a DATA message must be acknowledged by the collector. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrKeepAliveInterval.name: cadIpdrKeepAliveInterval
cadIpdrKeepAliveInterval.description: Maximum duration of protocol silence before a KEEPALIVE message must be sent.

cadIpdrExportAllCounts.name: cadIpdrExportAllCounts
cadIpdrExportAllCounts.description: Export all counts if true, and supress duplicate counts if false. The default is false. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrExportCpeInfo.name: cadIpdrExportCpeInfo
cadIpdrExportCpeInfo.description: Export information about CPEs behind CMs (CmCpeInfoList) if set to true. If false, supress information about CPEs. The default is false. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrSessionId.name: cadIpdrSessionId
cadIpdrSessionId.description: session-id used in the header of IPDR protocol messages. The default is 1. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrExportMode.name: cadIpdrExportMode
cadIpdrExportMode.description: DOCSIS mode exporter, either DOCSIS 2.0 or DOCSIS 3.0. The default is DOCSIS 2.0 mode, or 1.

cadIpdrCollectorTable.name: cadIpdrCollectorTable
cadIpdrCollectorTable.description: A priority ordered list of collectors that will be allowed to connect to the exporter. The highest priority active collector is designated the primary collector. This list is exclusive and any collector not in this list will be ignored. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorPriority.name: cadIpdrCollectorPriority
cadIpdrCollectorPriority.description: The collector priority. Lower values indicate higher priority. The default priority is 1. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorIpAddrType.name: cadIpdrCollectorIpAddrType
cadIpdrCollectorIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address (IPv4 or IPv6). The only internet address type currently allowed is IPv4. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorIpAddress.name: cadIpdrCollectorIpAddress
cadIpdrCollectorIpAddress.description: Source IP address of a collector that will be permitted to connect to the exporter. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorPort.name: cadIpdrCollectorPort
cadIpdrCollectorPort.description: Destination port of collector if exporter trys to connect to the collector. Default is 4747. This object is currently disabled. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorActive.name: cadIpdrCollectorActive
cadIpdrCollectorActive.description: True if this collector is connected to the exporter. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorPrimary.name: cadIpdrCollectorPrimary
cadIpdrCollectorPrimary.description: True if this collector is the primary collector. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorOutIntRecs.name: cadIpdrCollectorOutIntRecs
cadIpdrCollectorOutIntRecs.description: Number of interim data records exported to this collector. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorOutStpRecs.name: cadIpdrCollectorOutStpRecs
cadIpdrCollectorOutStpRecs.description: Number of stop data records exported to this collector. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorSupIntRecs.name: cadIpdrCollectorSupIntRecs
cadIpdrCollectorSupIntRecs.description: Number of interim data records suppressed for this collector. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrCollectorStatus.name: cadIpdrCollectorStatus
cadIpdrCollectorStatus.description: Row control for this collector. The only valid values for this object are createAndGo, destroy, and active. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportCycleTable.name: cadIpdrReportCycleTable
cadIpdrReportCycleTable.description: A list of scheduled report cycle start times and interval durations. Multiple entries indicate blocks of time with variable interval durations. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportStartHH.name: cadIpdrReportStartHH
cadIpdrReportStartHH.description: The report cycle start hour. The default is 00. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportStartMM.name: cadIpdrReportStartMM
cadIpdrReportStartMM.description: The report cycle start minutes after the hour. Default is 00. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportInterval.name: cadIpdrReportInterval
cadIpdrReportInterval.description: The report cycle interval duration in minutes. The default is 60 minutes. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportOutIntRecs.name: cadIpdrReportOutIntRecs
cadIpdrReportOutIntRecs.description: Number of interim data records exported during this report cycle. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportOutStpRecs.name: cadIpdrReportOutStpRecs
cadIpdrReportOutStpRecs.description: Number of stop data records exported during this report cycle. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportSupIntRecs.name: cadIpdrReportSupIntRecs
cadIpdrReportSupIntRecs.description: Number of interim data records suppressed during this report cycle. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportStatus.name: cadIpdrReportStatus
cadIpdrReportStatus.description: Row control for this report cycle. The only valid values for this object are createAndGo, destroy, and active. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 mode.

cadIpdrServiceTable.name: cadIpdrServiceTable
cadIpdrServiceTable.description: A session-id ordered list of services that will be allowed to be requested by the Collector. This list is exclusive and are used when the exporter is in DOCSIS 3.0 mode.

cadIpdrServiceSessionId.name: cadIpdrServiceSessionId
cadIpdrServiceSessionId.description: The session-id used in the header of IPDR protocol messages. The default is 1.

cadIpdrServiceType.name: cadIpdrServiceType
cadIpdrServiceType.description: The session service types are unknown(0), samis_1(1), samis_2(2), cpe(3), cm_reg(4), cm_us(5), spect(6), diag(7), topo(8), us_util(9), ds_util(10), diag_evt(11), diag_det(12), cm_sf(13), cpe_a2(14), mcast(15). The default is 1.

cadIpdrServiceMethod.name: cadIpdrServiceMethod
cadIpdrServiceMethod.description: The session service method (unknown, time, event, adhoc). The default is time.

cadIpdrServicePriority.name: cadIpdrServicePriority
cadIpdrServicePriority.description: The session priority. Lower values indicate higher priority. This object is not used.

cadIpdrServiceDataAckWindow.name: cadIpdrServiceDataAckWindow
cadIpdrServiceDataAckWindow.description: The session maximum number of unacknowledged IPDR/SP messages that may be outstanding to the collector.

cadIpdrServiceDataAckTimeout.name: cadIpdrServiceDataAckTimeout
cadIpdrServiceDataAckTimeout.description: The session maximum elapsed time before a DATA message must be acknowledged by the collector.

cadIpdrServiceAllCounts.name: cadIpdrServiceAllCounts
cadIpdrServiceAllCounts.description: Export all counts if true, and supress duplicate counts if false. The default is false.

cadIpdrServiceStatus.name: cadIpdrServiceStatus
cadIpdrServiceStatus.description: Row control for this service. The only valid values for this object are createAndGo, destroy, and active.

cadIpdrReportCycleSetTable.name: cadIpdrReportCycleSetTable
cadIpdrReportCycleSetTable.description: A list of sets of scheduled report cycle start times and interval durations. Multiple entries indicate blocks of time with variable interval durations. Applicable to DOCSIS 3.0 mode.

cadIpdrReportCycleSetSet.name: cadIpdrReportCycleSetSet
cadIpdrReportCycleSetSet.description: The report cycle set id number. The default is 1.

cadIpdrReportCycleSetStartHH.name: cadIpdrReportCycleSetStartHH
cadIpdrReportCycleSetStartHH.description: The report cycle set start hour. The default is 00.

cadIpdrReportCycleSetStartMM.name: cadIpdrReportCycleSetStartMM
cadIpdrReportCycleSetStartMM.description: The report cycle set start minutes after the hour. Default is 00.

cadIpdrReportCycleSetInterval.name: cadIpdrReportCycleSetInterval
cadIpdrReportCycleSetInterval.description: The report cycle set interval duration in minutes. The default is 60 minutes.

cadIpdrReportCycleSetStatus.name: cadIpdrReportCycleSetStatus
cadIpdrReportCycleSetStatus.description: Row control for this report cycle set entry. The only valid values for this object are createAndGo, destroy, and active.

cadIpdrCountsTable.name: cadIpdrCountsTable
cadIpdrCountsTable.description: A session-id/priority/collector ordered list of counts for all sessions. Applicable to DOCSIS 2.0 and 3.0 modes.

cadIpdrCountsSessionId.name: cadIpdrCountsSessionId
cadIpdrCountsSessionId.description: The counts session-id used in the header of IPDR protocol messages. The default is 1.

cadIpdrCountsCollectorPriority.name: cadIpdrCountsCollectorPriority
cadIpdrCountsCollectorPriority.description: The counts collector priority. Lower values indicate higher priority. The default priority is 1.

cadIpdrCountsCollectorIpAddress.name: cadIpdrCountsCollectorIpAddress
cadIpdrCountsCollectorIpAddress.description: The counts source IP address of a collector that will be permitted to connect to the exporter.

cadIpdrCountsStartHH.name: cadIpdrCountsStartHH
cadIpdrCountsStartHH.description: The counts report cycle start hour. The default is 00.

cadIpdrCountsStartMM.name: cadIpdrCountsStartMM
cadIpdrCountsStartMM.description: The counts report cycle start minutes after the hour. Default is 00.

cadIpdrCountsStartTime.name: cadIpdrCountsStartTime
cadIpdrCountsStartTime.description: The counts report cycle start time. Default is 0 length.

cadIpdrCountsStopTime.name: cadIpdrCountsStopTime
cadIpdrCountsStopTime.description: The counts report cycle stop time. Default is 0 length.

cadIpdrCountsIntRecs.name: cadIpdrCountsIntRecs
cadIpdrCountsIntRecs.description: Number of interim data records exported for this session-id to this collector.

cadIpdrCountsSupIntRecs.name: cadIpdrCountsSupIntRecs
cadIpdrCountsSupIntRecs.description: Number of interim data records suppressed for this session-id to this collector.

cadIpdrCountsStartRecs.name: cadIpdrCountsStartRecs
cadIpdrCountsStartRecs.description: Number of start data records exported for this session-id to this collector.

cadIpdrCountsStopRecs.name: cadIpdrCountsStopRecs
cadIpdrCountsStopRecs.description: Number of stop data records exported for this session-id to this collector.

cadIpdrCountsEventRecs.name: cadIpdrCountsEventRecs
cadIpdrCountsEventRecs.description: Number of event data records exported for this session-id to this collector.

cadIpdrCountsStatus.name: cadIpdrCountsStatus
cadIpdrCountsStatus.description: Row control for this counts entry. The only valid values for this object are createAndGo, destroy, and active.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorTable.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorTable
cadIpdrSessionCollectorTable.description: A session and priority ordered list of collectors that is used to track the Active and Primary status of the collector relative to this session. Applicable to DOCSIS 3.0 mode.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorSessionId.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorSessionId
cadIpdrSessionCollectorSessionId.description: The counts session-id used in the header of IPDR protocol messages. The default is 1.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorPriority.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorPriority
cadIpdrSessionCollectorPriority.description: The collector priority. Lower values indicate higher priority. The default priority is 1.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorIpAddrType.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorIpAddrType
cadIpdrSessionCollectorIpAddrType.description: The type of internet address (IPv4 or IPv6). The only internet address type currently allowed is IPv4.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorIpAddress.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorIpAddress
cadIpdrSessionCollectorIpAddress.description: Source IP address of a collector that will be permitted to connect to the exporter.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorPort.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorPort
cadIpdrSessionCollectorPort.description: Destination port of collector if exporter trys to connect to the collector. Default is 4747. This object is currently disabled.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorActive.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorActive
cadIpdrSessionCollectorActive.description: True if this collector is connected to the exporter for this session.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorPrimary.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorPrimary
cadIpdrSessionCollectorPrimary.description: True if this collector is the primary collector for this session.

cadIpdrSessionCollectorStatus.name: cadIpdrSessionCollectorStatus
cadIpdrSessionCollectorStatus.description: Row control for this collector. The only valid values for this object are createAndGo, destroy, and active.

cadIpdrMIBCompliance.name: cadIpdrMIBCompliance
cadIpdrMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the Arris IPDR implementation.
